WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:00:27.104 --> 00:00:29.357
Howdy there. Mr. Lee.

3
00:00:29.523 --> 00:00:31.776
What's this? Filipino New Year's?

4
00:00:32.360 --> 00:00:33.945
No. Why you say that?

5
00:00:34.028 --> 00:00:35.863
'Cause you're cooking a feast.

6
00:00:35.947 --> 00:00:38.449
I can smell it from the interstate.

7
00:00:38.783 --> 00:00:41.035
What is that? Barbecue?

8
00:00:41.244 --> 00:00:43.746
Yeah. But it not coming from here.

9
00:00:44.622 --> 00:00:46.249
What is that noise?

10
00:04:17.631 --> 00:04:20.217
What is your take on this. Jerry?

11
00:04:20.759 --> 00:04:23.261
The people will love it. Mr. President.

12
00:04:23.595 --> 00:04:28.183
Our conflict is whether we ambush
the 6:00 news or hold out for prime time.

13
00:04:28.350 --> 00:04:30.685
Screw the press.
This is a need-to-know situation.

14
00:04:30.769 --> 00:04:34.773
We should make it top secret.
and should move in with Defcon Four.

15
00:04:34.981 --> 00:04:36.858
We can't sit on this.

16
00:04:38.526 --> 00:04:40.987
General Casey. do you have an opinion?

17
00:04:42.364 --> 00:04:43.615
Well. sir...

18
00:04:43.782 --> 00:04:45.283
...do we know they are hostile?

19
00:04:45.367 --> 00:04:47.285
What do you mean?

20
00:04:47.702 --> 00:04:50.288
They have the planet surrounded
by thousands of warships!

21
00:04:50.372 --> 00:04:52.290
Do we know they're warships?

22
00:04:55.794 --> 00:04:58.880
Professor. what do we know about them?

23
00:05:00.550 --> 00:05:02.718
They're very advanced technologically.

24
00:05:02.802 --> 00:05:06.055
Which suggests. rightfully so.
that they're peaceful.

25
00:05:06.639 --> 00:05:11.018
An advanced civilization is.
by definition. not barbaric.

26
00:05:11.143 --> 00:05:12.645
Mr. President...

27
00:05:13.020 --> 00:05:14.564
...this is a great day.

28
00:05:14.647 --> 00:05:16.649
I and all my colleagues...

29
00:05:16.816 --> 00:05:18.568
...are extremely excited.

30
00:05:19.026 --> 00:05:19.944
Good.

31
00:05:21.153 --> 00:05:23.531
Extraterrestrial life.

32
00:05:24.657 --> 00:05:26.325
You're right. Jerry.

33
00:05:26.534 --> 00:05:29.036
The people are going to love it.

34
00:05:29.161 --> 00:05:31.539
This is a momentous occasion.

35
00:05:32.415 --> 00:05:33.249
Mr. President--

36
00:05:33.332 --> 00:05:35.167
We'll go all media on this.

37
00:05:35.334 --> 00:05:37.086
I'll wear my Cerruti suit.

38
00:05:37.253 --> 00:05:38.921
I'll need a good speech.

39
00:05:39.922 --> 00:05:41.340
Statesman-like...

40
00:05:41.674 --> 00:05:43.384
...historical and yet...

41
00:05:43.593 --> 00:05:45.595
...warm. neighborly.

42
00:05:45.761 --> 00:05:49.557
Abraham Lincoln meets
Leave it to Beaver. kind of thing.

43
00:05:51.058 --> 00:05:52.685
Are they too old-fashioned?

44
00:05:52.768 --> 00:05:54.353
No. I don't think so.

45
00:05:54.604 --> 00:05:58.065
This has got the colors but. no.
I don't think so.

46
00:05:58.191 --> 00:05:59.568
Not vivid enough.

47
00:05:59.776 --> 00:06:01.778
Nancy had this in the library.

48
00:06:01.945 --> 00:06:02.696
Yes. indeed.

49
00:06:02.779 --> 00:06:04.031
I don't think so.

50
00:06:04.114 --> 00:06:07.492
I thought perhaps the watered silk.
This week it's on sale.

51
00:06:07.868 --> 00:06:10.579
I hardly think I need worry about that.

52
00:06:10.704 --> 00:06:13.373
My husband is the leader of the free world.

53
00:06:14.583 --> 00:06:16.043
What do you think?

54
00:06:16.710 --> 00:06:20.756
Why don't you leave the Roosevelt Room
the way the Roosevelts wanted it.

55
00:06:21.465 --> 00:06:25.719
Because Eleanor Roosevelt was
too fond of chintz. That's why.

56
00:06:26.136 --> 00:06:28.222
Mother. this isn't your house.

57
00:06:28.388 --> 00:06:31.475
lf you're going to be a pest. I'll ignore you!

58
00:06:31.725 --> 00:06:32.851
Mrs. Dale?

59
00:06:55.290 --> 00:06:57.960
I saw you fight Sonny Liston in '69.

60
00:06:58.127 --> 00:06:59.212
Really?

61
00:06:59.379 --> 00:07:01.548
You were a nun back then?

62
00:07:01.714 --> 00:07:04.884
We've always been fight fans.
haven't we sisters?

63
00:07:05.218 --> 00:07:07.470
Byron Williams. telephone.

64
00:07:07.637 --> 00:07:08.721
I must go.

65
00:07:08.888 --> 00:07:11.391
You ladies have a nice time.

66
00:07:17.021 --> 00:07:18.356
Oh. Louise.

67
00:07:18.898 --> 00:07:21.067
Sorry to call you at work. but...

68
00:07:21.568 --> 00:07:25.738
...the boys haven't been home
in two nights. I don't know what to do.

69
00:07:25.905 --> 00:07:27.991
You're doing the best you can.

70
00:07:28.241 --> 00:07:29.993
They're just at that age.

71
00:07:32.078 --> 00:07:35.540
The casino manager's giving me
the evil eye. I've gotta go.

72
00:07:35.665 --> 00:07:37.417
I'll call you later. okay?

73
00:07:38.251 --> 00:07:41.421
Are you still cool on me
coming to Washington?

74
00:07:41.588 --> 00:07:43.256
'Course I am.

75
00:07:43.756 --> 00:07:46.342
You take care. okay? Bye.

76
00:08:02.276 --> 00:08:04.111
Must you drink in front of me?

77
00:08:04.194 --> 00:08:06.280
You're an adult. Just cope.

78
00:08:06.447 --> 00:08:09.617
It doesn't help me
that all we ever do is sit in bars.

79
00:08:09.783 --> 00:08:11.619
This is work. baby. okay?

80
00:08:11.785 --> 00:08:15.456
I'm checking the decor.
the lighting. the traffic flow.

81
00:08:15.623 --> 00:08:18.626
lf I'd known you'd turn into a crook.
I wouldn't have married you.

82
00:08:18.709 --> 00:08:20.628
I'm not a crook.

83
00:08:20.794 --> 00:08:22.963
I'm ambitious. There's a difference.

84
00:08:23.047 --> 00:08:25.799
lf you think you can make
a nickel in this town...

85
00:08:25.883 --> 00:08:29.637
...without knowing how to dally
around a few curves. well...

86
00:08:29.970 --> 00:08:32.640
...you know nothing
of the gambling industry.

87
00:08:34.141 --> 00:08:38.229
The Galaxy's going to be
the best hotel in Vegas.

88
00:08:38.395 --> 00:08:40.064
The best!

89
00:08:40.272 --> 00:08:41.148
I promise.

90
00:08:41.232 --> 00:08:43.817
But don't you realize what you're doing?
You're destroying the Earth!

91
00:08:43.901 --> 00:08:46.820
All this greed! This money system!

92
00:08:46.987 --> 00:08:49.156
You're destroying everything!

93
00:08:49.907 --> 00:08:51.825
Okay. Barbara. okay.

94
00:08:52.159 --> 00:08:54.245
Keep your voice down.

95
00:08:54.995 --> 00:08:56.997
I got friends here.

96
00:08:58.333 --> 00:08:59.292
Sugar!

97
00:08:59.668 --> 00:09:01.086
Hit me one more time.

98
00:09:01.169 --> 00:09:02.587
Stop flirting with the waitress.

99
00:09:02.671 --> 00:09:04.005
God. Here.

100
00:09:05.590 --> 00:09:07.342
Go over to the roulette...

101
00:09:08.927 --> 00:09:10.679
...play our anniversary...

102
00:09:10.762 --> 00:09:12.847
...and stay off of black.

103
00:09:16.017 --> 00:09:16.851
Thanks.

104
00:09:25.402 --> 00:09:28.071
Make it quick.
we go out live in ten minutes.

105
00:09:28.905 --> 00:09:31.283
What? The actual president?

106
00:09:31.491 --> 00:09:32.659
Cutting in?

107
00:09:36.913 --> 00:09:40.083
Budget negotiations may be dead
in the water after this week.

108
00:09:40.166 --> 00:09:41.793
Hair looks good.

109
00:09:43.169 --> 00:09:44.254
I like the hair.

110
00:09:44.337 --> 00:09:46.506
...quote. ''factually-challenged. ''

111
00:09:47.340 --> 00:09:49.092
Yeah. Stone. Speak.

112
00:09:49.259 --> 00:09:50.760
Jason. hi. it's me.

113
00:09:51.928 --> 00:09:53.388
You wearing a bra?

114
00:09:53.847 --> 00:09:57.642
Listen. this is big. President Dale
is cutting into my show today.

115
00:09:59.270 --> 00:10:02.148
That's absurd. Why would he stoop
to being on ''Today in Fashion''?

116
00:10:02.231 --> 00:10:03.691
He's interrupting everybody.

117
00:10:03.774 --> 00:10:07.194
I don't know. it's some sort of
an emergency announcement.

118
00:10:07.361 --> 00:10:10.072
This doesn't make sense.
He should talk to us.

119
00:10:11.115 --> 00:10:13.159
White House is coming out live.

120
00:10:14.118 --> 00:10:16.954
Good evening. my fellow Americans.

121
00:10:17.288 --> 00:10:20.958
I apologize for interrupting
your regular programs...

122
00:10:21.125 --> 00:10:24.128
...but I have a very important
announcement to make.

123
00:10:24.629 --> 00:10:27.715
Many important things have happened
to me in my life:

124
00:10:28.216 --> 00:10:30.468
My graduation from Princeton...

125
00:10:30.968 --> 00:10:34.472
...the day that Marsha said
she would be my wife...

126
00:10:34.639 --> 00:10:36.891
...the birth of our daughter Taffy.

127
00:10:37.058 --> 00:10:38.059
Thanks. Dad.

128
00:10:38.142 --> 00:10:42.813
And the news that I have heard today
ranks right up there.

129
00:10:43.064 --> 00:10:45.316
A powerful memory is in the making.

130
00:10:45.983 --> 00:10:47.735
Not just for me...

131
00:10:47.902 --> 00:10:49.737
...but for all mankind.

132
00:10:50.029 --> 00:10:51.030
Today...

133
00:10:51.072 --> 00:10:54.659
...an extraordinary discovery
was made by the Hubble telescope.

134
00:10:56.787 --> 00:10:59.706
The data from the Hubble was decoded...

135
00:11:00.541 --> 00:11:05.170
...then analyzed by the most
powerful computers at MIT.

136
00:11:05.796 --> 00:11:08.048
The images are undeniable.

137
00:11:08.549 --> 00:11:11.718
We are entering the dawn of a new era.

138
00:11:12.886 --> 00:11:16.723
Frame enlargements provide
an astonishing sight.

139
00:11:16.974 --> 00:11:21.562
A fleet of vehicles.
which can best be described as...

140
00:11:21.812 --> 00:11:23.397
...flying saucers.

141
00:11:23.564 --> 00:11:26.733
Come on! Come on!
Papa needs a new pair of shoes!

142
00:11:29.736 --> 00:11:32.406
Hey. am I the only one
shooting craps here?

143
00:11:32.573 --> 00:11:36.285
We hope we will have the chance
to meet with them.

144
00:11:36.451 --> 00:11:39.204
This is the perfect summation
to the 20th Century....

145
00:11:39.288 --> 00:11:40.706
Martians.

146
00:11:41.290 --> 00:11:43.208
This is great.

147
00:11:43.625 --> 00:11:46.378
Please. come to Earth. Please.

148
00:11:47.045 --> 00:11:48.380
We need you.

149
00:11:52.551 --> 00:11:54.636
I got people coming in!

150
00:11:54.803 --> 00:11:57.639
Everybody wants to be part of this.

151
00:11:57.724 --> 00:12:00.560
Galaxy's going to be world class.

152
00:12:01.644 --> 00:12:02.979
And soon...

153
00:12:03.146 --> 00:12:06.149
...we will become one solar system.

154
00:12:06.649 --> 00:12:07.984
What the hell's he talking about?

155
00:12:08.067 --> 00:12:10.653
These flying saucers
have come from Mars...

156
00:12:12.405 --> 00:12:14.991
...and at their current course and speed...

157
00:12:15.325 --> 00:12:16.993
...will enter Earth's orbit in 16 hours.

158
00:12:17.076 --> 00:12:20.997
I've been thinking about Martians
when there weren't any.

159
00:12:21.414 --> 00:12:26.002
It is profoundly moving to know
there is intelligent life out there.

160
00:12:26.169 --> 00:12:27.670
Glad it's somewhere.

161
00:12:27.754 --> 00:12:31.591
Our world
will never feel quite the same again.

162
00:12:33.176 --> 00:12:34.427
Good night...

163
00:12:35.428 --> 00:12:37.305
...and God bless you all.

164
00:12:47.857 --> 00:12:49.192
This...

165
00:12:50.109 --> 00:12:51.694
...is intense.

166
00:12:54.364 --> 00:12:56.449
Shut up. Poppy. Shut up.

167
00:12:57.534 --> 00:12:58.869
Shut up!

168
00:12:59.536 --> 00:13:00.746
Jason Stone.

169
00:13:03.624 --> 00:13:04.875
It's for you.

170
00:13:06.710 --> 00:13:09.213
Poppy. honey. No. sweetie.

171
00:13:10.881 --> 00:13:13.050
That's right. Good girl.

172
00:13:16.971 --> 00:13:18.597
I could be there at...

173
00:13:19.223 --> 00:13:21.225
...I don't know. 11:00.

174
00:13:36.657 --> 00:13:40.160
They want me to interview
the professor from the White House.

175
00:13:40.828 --> 00:13:41.870
Kessler?

176
00:13:43.497 --> 00:13:44.582
Donald Kessler?

177
00:13:44.665 --> 00:13:46.709
Yeah. I think that was his name.

178
00:13:47.543 --> 00:13:48.919
You know. the science guy.

179
00:13:49.003 --> 00:13:50.838
This is nuts. this is....

180
00:13:51.171 --> 00:13:53.090
We should have got that guy.

181
00:13:53.507 --> 00:13:55.676
Your people are too slow.

182
00:13:57.012 --> 00:13:58.263
Right. Poppy?

183
00:14:22.120 --> 00:14:23.121
Finished!

184
00:14:23.204 --> 00:14:25.040
One minute. 57 seconds.

185
00:14:26.541 --> 00:14:28.793
-Didn't I tell you under two minutes?
-You did!

186
00:14:28.877 --> 00:14:29.878
You did!

187
00:14:29.961 --> 00:14:31.046
Hot damn.

188
00:14:31.796 --> 00:14:33.173
Want a doughnut?

189
00:14:33.465 --> 00:14:34.549
How old are they?

190
00:14:34.633 --> 00:14:36.051
Fresh baked. Monday.

191
00:14:36.134 --> 00:14:38.803
Richie. that's six days ago!

192
00:14:39.304 --> 00:14:40.722
Give me a couple.

193
00:14:44.476 --> 00:14:46.895
This Martian thing is pretty awesome.

194
00:14:47.062 --> 00:14:50.815
Did one of you traitors see my Muffy?

195
00:14:50.982 --> 00:14:52.734
Your brother's volunteering.

196
00:14:52.817 --> 00:14:54.986
As soon as I get back to the base.

197
00:14:55.070 --> 00:14:56.321
Volunteer for what?

198
00:14:56.405 --> 00:14:57.907
Martian detail.

199
00:14:58.991 --> 00:14:59.825
Cool.

200
00:14:59.909 --> 00:15:03.496
lf any Martians come around here.
I'll kick their butts!

201
00:15:15.925 --> 00:15:16.926
Jump!

202
00:15:26.477 --> 00:15:28.980
Folks.
we must make an unscheduled stop!

203
00:15:32.358 --> 00:15:33.526
It's Mama.

204
00:15:34.277 --> 00:15:37.530
Why are you here?
lf you ain't home. why ain't you in class?

205
00:15:37.613 --> 00:15:38.698
Class was cancelled.

206
00:15:38.781 --> 00:15:40.199
It was not!

207
00:15:40.366 --> 00:15:41.367
-Come here!
-Why?

208
00:15:41.450 --> 00:15:43.244
I'm not going to hurt you.

209
00:15:43.703 --> 00:15:44.954
Let go of him.

210
00:15:46.539 --> 00:15:48.958
Okay. Now just come here.

211
00:15:49.292 --> 00:15:50.543
Come here.

212
00:15:51.794 --> 00:15:53.462
Think it's smart to cut school?

213
00:15:53.546 --> 00:15:55.464
-What are you doing?
-Do you?

214
00:15:56.466 --> 00:15:57.634
No. it's dumb.

215
00:15:57.718 --> 00:15:59.553
You'll flunk! Go to jail!

216
00:15:59.720 --> 00:16:01.555
Get on the bus!

217
00:16:01.722 --> 00:16:02.806
Get on!

218
00:16:03.056 --> 00:16:05.559
I'll be tripping on you. Get back there.

219
00:16:05.726 --> 00:16:07.311
I don't want to hear anymore.

220
00:16:07.394 --> 00:16:08.478
I hate school.

221
00:16:08.562 --> 00:16:09.813
I heard that!

222
00:16:33.670 --> 00:16:34.755
Hi. there.

223
00:16:34.838 --> 00:16:36.006
Want a date?

224
00:16:36.173 --> 00:16:37.591
How about it?

225
00:16:37.841 --> 00:16:39.176
A date?

226
00:16:41.511 --> 00:16:42.804
It sounds good.

227
00:16:45.015 --> 00:16:46.850
The stress at work is...

228
00:16:47.184 --> 00:16:48.769
...unbelievable.

229
00:16:54.233 --> 00:16:55.984
May I speak to you in private?

230
00:16:56.069 --> 00:16:58.863
No. I must watch the floor.
What do you want?

231
00:16:59.364 --> 00:17:02.992
-I'm supporting a family back east.
-I thought you were divorced.

232
00:17:03.076 --> 00:17:05.870
I am. but I still have to take care of them.

233
00:17:06.746 --> 00:17:09.874
Things have been a little lean around here.

234
00:17:10.041 --> 00:17:12.001
I was wondering if I could get a raise?

235
00:17:12.085 --> 00:17:13.294
Out of the question.

236
00:17:13.378 --> 00:17:16.589
I'm an asset to this hotel.
They like me around here.

237
00:17:16.756 --> 00:17:18.424
You're a nice guy.

238
00:17:18.758 --> 00:17:22.595
But I can get Leon Spinks
or Buster Douglas for the same money.

239
00:17:23.054 --> 00:17:25.932
You better get moving.
You're on in five minutes.

240
00:17:35.108 --> 00:17:37.610
This show's going to get a great rating.

241
00:17:38.403 --> 00:17:39.696
It's all yours.

242
00:17:40.613 --> 00:17:45.577
ln certain circumstances the proposition
that two and two equals five...

243
00:17:45.743 --> 00:17:47.579
...is entirely legitimate.

244
00:17:49.289 --> 00:17:50.707
Call me Nathalie.

245
00:17:51.124 --> 00:17:53.918
And you. do please call me Donald.

246
00:17:55.296 --> 00:17:56.797
I admire your show.

247
00:17:59.258 --> 00:18:01.760
Really? You like my work?

248
00:18:02.136 --> 00:18:04.096
Yes. Very much.

249
00:18:04.263 --> 00:18:05.598
Why....

250
00:18:06.140 --> 00:18:07.933
Thank you.

251
00:18:08.100 --> 00:18:09.852
Coming out of commercial.

252
00:18:09.935 --> 00:18:11.645
In five...four...

253
00:18:11.812 --> 00:18:13.480
...three...two....

254
00:18:13.564 --> 00:18:16.984
Welcome back.
We're with Professor Donald Kessler.

255
00:18:18.944 --> 00:18:22.114
He's the chairman
of the American Academy...

256
00:18:22.281 --> 00:18:24.658
...of Astronautics.

257
00:18:25.826 --> 00:18:27.161
Professor...

258
00:18:27.453 --> 00:18:30.831
...isn't it weird that we sent
a space probe to Mars...

259
00:18:30.998 --> 00:18:33.083
...and we didn't even find anyone?

260
00:18:33.167 --> 00:18:35.169
Well. not really...

261
00:18:35.336 --> 00:18:36.545
...Nathalie.

262
00:18:37.004 --> 00:18:39.340
We didn't get into the canals.

263
00:18:39.506 --> 00:18:41.550
The Martian canals are canyons.

264
00:18:41.800 --> 00:18:43.969
Some are over 100 miles deep.

265
00:18:44.178 --> 00:18:49.016
The Martian civilization has clearly
developed under the planet's surface.

266
00:18:49.350 --> 00:18:52.895
Their science and technology
must be absolutely mind-boggling.

267
00:18:53.687 --> 00:18:54.605
So...

268
00:18:54.688 --> 00:18:56.690
...what in your view. Donald...

269
00:18:57.359 --> 00:18:58.443
