299
00:20:41.172 --> 00:20:42.673
Look at that brain.

300
00:20:43.257 --> 00:20:44.842
He must be real smart.

301
00:20:45.009 --> 00:20:47.011
It's gross!

302
00:20:47.762 --> 00:20:49.513
Don't forget. Nathalie...

303
00:20:49.680 --> 00:20:52.266
...that we will look equally gross to him.

304
00:20:57.272 --> 00:20:59.441
He made the international sign
of the doughnut.

305
00:21:00.025 --> 00:21:04.363
From the limited information available.
I've made three extrapolations. One:

306
00:21:04.529 --> 00:21:07.366
Our Martian friend
is a carbon-based life form.

307
00:21:07.532 --> 00:21:09.701
Two: He breathes nitrogen.

308
00:21:09.868 --> 00:21:10.953
And three:

309
00:21:11.036 --> 00:21:14.039
The large cerebrum here. indicates...

310
00:21:14.539 --> 00:21:16.458
...telepathic potential.

311
00:21:16.875 --> 00:21:18.377
You mean they can...

312
00:21:18.460 --> 00:21:20.045
...read our thoughts?

313
00:21:21.630 --> 00:21:23.131
Potentially. yes.

314
00:21:23.298 --> 00:21:25.467
What about their intentions?

315
00:21:25.634 --> 00:21:27.302
Are they friendly people?

316
00:21:27.386 --> 00:21:32.224
Logic dictates that given
their high level of technical development...

317
00:21:32.558 --> 00:21:34.476
...they're an advanced culture.

318
00:21:34.560 --> 00:21:37.396
Therefore. peaceful and enlightened.

319
00:21:38.230 --> 00:21:40.566
The human race. on the other hand...

320
00:21:40.983 --> 00:21:43.986
...is an aggressively dangerous species.

321
00:21:44.903 --> 00:21:47.990
Now I suspect they have
more to fear from us...

322
00:21:48.156 --> 00:21:49.741
...than we from them.

323
00:21:50.576 --> 00:21:51.577
Doctor.

324
00:21:51.994 --> 00:21:53.120
Thank you.

325
00:21:54.246 --> 00:21:58.083
For many years.
I've been refining a translating computer.

326
00:21:59.002 --> 00:22:01.921
The results are not perfect. but this...

327
00:22:02.088 --> 00:22:04.424
...may answer some of your questions.

328
00:22:10.221 --> 00:22:11.806
Green skin...

329
00:22:12.557 --> 00:22:14.726
...800 centuries ago.

330
00:22:15.143 --> 00:22:16.728
Their bodily fluids...

331
00:22:16.895 --> 00:22:19.397
...include the birth of half-breeds.

332
00:22:19.814 --> 00:22:21.357
How many centuries did he say?

333
00:22:21.441 --> 00:22:22.442
Eight hundred. sir.

334
00:22:22.525 --> 00:22:24.819
Self-determination of the cosmos.

335
00:22:25.820 --> 00:22:28.406
For dark is the suede that...

336
00:22:28.573 --> 00:22:29.741
...mows...

337
00:22:29.991 --> 00:22:32.076
...like a harvest.

338
00:22:32.660 --> 00:22:34.621
What the hell does that mean?

339
00:22:49.677 --> 00:22:50.845
Hey. Mitch.

340
00:22:50.929 --> 00:22:52.222
Good morning.

341
00:22:52.347 --> 00:22:55.934
I'm sorry. you can't come this way.
There's a tour in progress.

342
00:23:04.944 --> 00:23:06.737
Hello. my name is Barbara.

343
00:23:06.820 --> 00:23:08.489
Hello. Barbara.

344
00:23:09.156 --> 00:23:13.327
I am an alcoholic.
but I haven't had a drink in three months.

345
00:23:19.959 --> 00:23:23.295
I'm feeling so optimistic
because of the Martians.

346
00:23:23.963 --> 00:23:26.382
We're not alone in the universe.

347
00:23:26.715 --> 00:23:28.717
And it's so perfect...

348
00:23:28.884 --> 00:23:32.429
...that it's happening at the beginning
of the new millennium.

349
00:23:32.638 --> 00:23:34.557
Our planet was suffering...

350
00:23:34.723 --> 00:23:38.143
...with the ozone and the rain forest and...

351
00:23:39.728 --> 00:23:42.898
...so many people unhappy in their lives.

352
00:23:43.649 --> 00:23:44.817
And then...

353
00:23:45.484 --> 00:23:49.071
...the Martians heard
our global karmic cry for help.

354
00:23:49.655 --> 00:23:51.156
People say they're ugly...

355
00:23:51.240 --> 00:23:53.993
...but I think they've come
to show us the way.

356
00:23:56.079 --> 00:23:58.415
I think they've come to save us.

357
00:24:01.376 --> 00:24:02.502
Thank you.

358
00:24:15.181 --> 00:24:16.266
Bye-bye.

359
00:24:16.349 --> 00:24:19.269
You be careful. Don't get yourself killed.

360
00:24:19.436 --> 00:24:20.854
Ain't she cute?

361
00:24:21.021 --> 00:24:23.440
-We're real proud of you.
-Thanks. Dad.

362
00:24:24.774 --> 00:24:26.192
Let me take this.

363
00:24:27.694 --> 00:24:31.698
So long. retard. Don't touch
any of my stuff while I'm gone.

364
00:24:33.783 --> 00:24:35.201
Bye-bye. Grandma.

365
00:24:35.368 --> 00:24:36.620
Good-bye. Thomas.

366
00:24:36.703 --> 00:24:38.121
It's Billy-Glenn. Grandma.

367
00:24:38.204 --> 00:24:39.789
I know. Thomas.

368
00:24:41.708 --> 00:24:43.043
Bye-bye. honey.

369
00:24:44.544 --> 00:24:46.046
I must go.

370
00:24:59.227 --> 00:25:00.770
Take care of my boy.

371
00:25:11.906 --> 00:25:13.074
He'll be all right.

372
