500
00:35:18.898 --> 00:35:19.815
Jason Stone...

501
00:35:19.899 --> 00:35:21.234
...GNN...

502
00:35:21.400 --> 00:35:22.443
...Pahrump.

503
00:35:55.477 --> 00:35:56.645
Some room.

504
00:35:56.812 --> 00:35:58.605
Give them room.

505
00:36:50.490 --> 00:36:52.701
It is an awesome sight.

506
00:36:52.868 --> 00:36:55.829
The giant spacecraft glinting...

507
00:36:55.997 --> 00:36:58.666
...in the Nevada sun like a...

508
00:36:59.334 --> 00:37:00.668
...giant...

509
00:37:01.169 --> 00:37:02.670
...hubcap.

510
00:37:04.339 --> 00:37:06.007
Something's happening.

511
00:37:11.679 --> 00:37:13.056
The doorway...

512
00:37:13.223 --> 00:37:14.474
...is opening.

513
00:37:18.686 --> 00:37:20.563
A silver ramp...

514
00:37:20.730 --> 00:37:22.232
...is coming out...

515
00:37:23.191 --> 00:37:25.026
...like a giant tongue.

516
00:37:49.092 --> 00:37:50.760
Gee whiz.

517
00:38:19.081 --> 00:38:20.416
Martians!

518
00:38:21.417 --> 00:38:23.127
Funny little critters.

519
00:39:02.000 --> 00:39:03.168
Well?

520
00:39:04.127 --> 00:39:05.045
Wait.

521
00:39:08.798 --> 00:39:09.925
Greetings.

522
00:39:10.133 --> 00:39:12.636
I am the Martian ambassador.

523
00:39:15.138 --> 00:39:17.807
Everything is fixed now. You may speak.

524
00:39:17.974 --> 00:39:19.309
Greetings.

525
00:39:19.476 --> 00:39:21.061
I am General Casey...

526
00:39:21.144 --> 00:39:25.815
...Commanding Officer of the Armed
Forces of the United States of America.

527
00:39:26.191 --> 00:39:28.818
On behalf of the people of Earth:

528
00:39:28.985 --> 00:39:30.028
Welcome.

529
00:39:30.862 --> 00:39:32.280
He did that well.

530
00:40:02.562 --> 00:40:04.063
We come in peace.

531
00:40:04.897 --> 00:40:07.066
We come in peace. We come in peace.

532
00:40:11.988 --> 00:40:14.156
They came in peace.

533
00:40:17.326 --> 00:40:18.995
We come in peace.

534
00:40:48.357 --> 00:40:49.442
Open fire!

535
00:41:21.058 --> 00:41:22.226
What?

536
00:42:11.859 --> 00:42:14.362
Die. you alien shithead!

537
00:42:20.952 --> 00:42:22.161
I surrender!

538
00:42:29.794 --> 00:42:32.380
No. it ain't happening! It didn't happen!

539
00:43:29.230 --> 00:43:31.398
Holy Mother of God!

540
00:43:32.066 --> 00:43:33.525
Did you see that?

541
00:43:33.692 --> 00:43:37.154
We should hit these assholes
with everything we've got. sir.

542
00:43:37.738 --> 00:43:39.281
Sir. Mr. President.
I know this seems terrible...

543
00:43:39.365 --> 00:43:41.325
...but let's not be too rash.

544
00:43:41.408 --> 00:43:42.952
We should nuke them!

545
00:43:43.410 --> 00:43:46.205
We must establish
a line of communication first.

546
00:43:46.872 --> 00:43:48.582
Set up a town hall.

547
00:43:48.749 --> 00:43:50.793
We'll get the public's opinion.

548
00:43:52.754 --> 00:43:54.547
What do you think?

549
00:43:56.258 --> 00:43:58.051
Kick the crap out of them.

550
00:43:59.552 --> 00:44:01.179
Ladies and gentlemen...

551
00:44:01.263 --> 00:44:03.807
...it may be a cultural misunderstanding.

552
00:44:04.557 --> 00:44:06.560
Maybe to them. doves mean war.

553
00:44:08.478 --> 00:44:11.481
We all saw how they reacted to that dove.

554
00:44:11.815 --> 00:44:13.316
It frightened them.

555
00:44:13.733 --> 00:44:15.902
He did say that...

556
00:44:17.904 --> 00:44:20.073
...''We come in peace.''

557
00:44:29.916 --> 00:44:32.002
The new computer's ready.

558
00:44:32.168 --> 00:44:34.170
Okay. let's do it.

559
00:44:34.337 --> 00:44:36.923
I know we're making the right decision.

560
00:44:39.926 --> 00:44:41.428
Ready to transmit.

561
00:44:43.513 --> 00:44:47.267
This is the president of the United States.

562
00:44:48.184 --> 00:44:50.020
I'm speaking in the hope...

563
00:44:50.186 --> 00:44:53.565
...that what happened earlier today
in the Nevada desert...

564
00:44:53.941 --> 00:44:57.111
...was a cultural misunderstanding.

565
00:44:57.945 --> 00:45:00.865
There can be no doubt
that we two peoples...

566
00:45:01.032 --> 00:45:04.285
...have a great deal to offer one another.

567
00:45:04.452 --> 00:45:06.454
You must be as excited as we...

568
00:45:06.621 --> 00:45:09.832
...to find intelligent life in the solar system.

569
00:45:10.958 --> 00:45:12.877
Let me make it clear.

570
00:45:13.044 --> 00:45:14.712
You have nothing...

571
00:45:14.879 --> 00:45:16.881
...to fear from us.

572
00:45:17.298 --> 00:45:20.468
Our customs may be strange to you...

573
00:45:20.635 --> 00:45:23.304
...but we mean no harm.

574
00:46:35.294 --> 00:46:37.879
When the investors fly in...

575
00:46:38.380 --> 00:46:41.049
...I would like for them each to be...

576
00:46:42.384 --> 00:46:43.885
...met by a limo.

577
00:46:44.886 --> 00:46:47.306
Top of the line cars...

578
00:46:47.889 --> 00:46:50.225
...leather interiors...

579
00:46:50.809 --> 00:46:53.228
...Corinthian. if they got it.

580
00:46:54.063 --> 00:46:57.483
Are you still spinning your wheels
on that cockamamie hotel?

581
00:46:58.902 --> 00:47:00.153
Hello!

582
00:47:00.820 --> 00:47:02.822
The Martians have attacked!

583
00:47:02.989 --> 00:47:07.076
This was no misunderstanding.
I was there. I saw it.

584
00:47:07.243 --> 00:47:09.662
Look. you're worried about yesterday.

585
00:47:09.996 --> 00:47:11.998
I'm worried about tomorrow.

586
00:47:12.165 --> 00:47:15.752
The Martians land on Earth.
they'll need a place to stay.

587
00:47:15.919 --> 00:47:17.629
Just like everyone else.

588
00:47:18.421 --> 00:47:19.923
My God.

589
00:47:21.257 --> 00:47:24.010
Maybe we should all be destroyed.

590
00:47:25.011 --> 00:47:28.181
The human race doesn't deserve to live.

591
00:47:35.188 --> 00:47:36.356
Ethel...

592
00:47:36.522 --> 00:47:38.274
...that reminds me.

593
00:47:38.441 --> 00:47:40.860
I'd like the limos to be stocked...

594
00:47:41.027 --> 00:47:44.113
...with every kind of alcohol
known to man.

595
00:47:44.280 --> 00:47:47.033
And top it off with a bottle of Dom...

596
00:47:47.200 --> 00:47:48.701
...on ice.

597
00:47:49.702 --> 00:47:52.956
What confounds me most of all
is the lack of genitalia.

598
00:47:53.123 --> 00:47:55.042
Down here is the aorta.

599
00:47:55.209 --> 00:47:57.711
Up here we have the sphinx.

600
00:47:58.045 --> 00:48:01.215
Notice the highly developed
nerve system here.

601
00:48:01.382 --> 00:48:04.885
This explains. of course.
the cerebral arteries.

602
00:48:05.052 --> 00:48:08.722
And if we notice down here.
behind the optic chiasm...

603
00:48:09.473 --> 00:48:11.558
...several glands....

604
00:48:15.312 --> 00:48:17.147
Very curious.

605
00:48:59.774 --> 00:49:04.362
''He who believes in me.
though he die. yet shall he live.

606
00:49:05.280 --> 00:49:09.284
''And whoever lives and believes in me
shall never die.''

607
00:49:10.452 --> 00:49:13.788
Billy-Glenn Norris gave his life
defending our country.

608
00:49:13.955 --> 00:49:15.874
Why did it have to be him?

609
00:49:16.041 --> 00:49:20.045
He's a true American hero.
May God rest his soul.

610
00:49:21.713 --> 00:49:23.548
Ready! Aim.

611
00:49:25.133 --> 00:49:26.134
Fire!

612
00:49:27.552 --> 00:49:28.637
Aim!

613
00:49:28.970 --> 00:49:30.055
Fire!

614
00:49:42.734 --> 00:49:43.944
Hello?

615
00:49:44.110 --> 00:49:47.489
Byron! Is everything all right?
You still coming tomorrow?

616
00:49:47.572 --> 00:49:51.076
Just try and stop me.
That plane arrives at 4:00 p.m.

617
00:49:51.284 --> 00:49:52.786
Are the kids there?

618
00:49:52.954 --> 00:49:54.288
Yeah. hold on.

619
00:49:57.458 --> 00:49:59.126
-Me first.
-No. me.

620
00:50:02.755 --> 00:50:03.547
Hey. Dad.

621
00:50:03.631 --> 00:50:05.633
Who's that? Neville?

622
00:50:06.300 --> 00:50:07.301
How are you?

623
00:50:07.385 --> 00:50:09.303
We're going to the White House.

624
00:50:09.387 --> 00:50:10.972
The White House?

625
00:50:11.138 --> 00:50:12.390
Yeah. tomorrow.

626
00:50:12.556 --> 00:50:14.558
-Give it back!
-Leave me alone.

627
00:50:14.725 --> 00:50:16.978
It's a school thing. like a tour.

628
00:50:17.144 --> 00:50:20.064
So you're still going to school
once in a while?

629
00:50:21.566 --> 00:50:22.984
Give me your ma again.

630
00:50:23.067 --> 00:50:24.068
Hold on.

631
00:50:24.151 --> 00:50:24.986
Mom.

632
00:50:25.236 --> 00:50:27.989
-You always get to the phone first.
-So what?

633
00:50:28.656 --> 00:50:30.241
I'm first to the game.

634
00:50:32.326 --> 00:50:35.413
Why are you wasting this phone time?
I'll see you tomorrow.

635
00:50:35.496 --> 00:50:38.082
But there's something
I want to say to you.

636
00:50:38.249 --> 00:50:40.668
Just 'cause I feel like saying it.

637
00:50:40.918 --> 00:50:42.128
What's that?

638
00:50:42.837 --> 00:50:44.255
I love you.

639
00:50:46.090 --> 00:50:47.925
I love you too. Byron.

640
00:50:48.092 --> 00:50:51.178
Now stop wasting money!
I'll see you tomorrow!

641
00:51:08.697 --> 00:51:10.198
They're responding.

642
00:51:13.535 --> 00:51:15.537
A message from the Martians.

643
00:51:17.956 --> 00:51:18.874
Really?

644
00:51:18.957 --> 00:51:21.043
They've issued a formal apology.

645
00:51:22.961 --> 00:51:25.047
This is great!

646
00:51:25.797 --> 00:51:27.716
I told you this would happen.

647
00:51:27.883 --> 00:51:32.054
The Martian ambassador feels terrible
and wants to speak to Congress.

648
00:51:32.220 --> 00:51:33.805
That's good. isn't it?

649
00:51:33.972 --> 00:51:35.474
You bet.

650
00:51:36.058 --> 00:51:38.393
It's a victory for our administration.

651
00:52:52.970 --> 00:52:54.555
Ladies and gentlemen.

652
00:52:54.722 --> 00:52:57.808
This is a proud day for all Americans.

653
00:52:58.392 --> 00:53:01.645
This is a hell of a photo-op. Jerry.

654
00:53:02.229 --> 00:53:04.398
Are you sure I shouldn't be there?

655
00:53:04.565 --> 00:53:08.319
The Secret Service don't want
the executive branch...

656
00:53:08.485 --> 00:53:11.572
...and the legislative branch
in the same room.

657
00:53:12.656 --> 00:53:15.659
The Martian ambassador
is going to say a few words.

658
00:53:16.243 --> 00:53:18.412
Come on down. Mr. Ambassador!

659
00:54:26.481 --> 00:54:28.191
Mr. Ambassador. please!

660
00:54:33.989 --> 00:54:34.990
Please!

661
00:54:35.240 --> 00:54:37.158
This doesn't make sense!

662
00:54:37.325 --> 00:54:39.327
It's not logical! It's not--

663
00:54:41.329 --> 00:54:43.081
Guess it wasn't the dove.

664
00:54:45.000 --> 00:54:45.917
Fire!

665
00:54:51.757 --> 00:54:53.759
They blew up Congress!

666
00:55:15.865 --> 00:55:17.950
Why'd they do that?

667
00:55:18.159 --> 00:55:21.037
Maybe they don't like the human being.

668
00:55:39.013 --> 00:55:40.514
Hello. gentlemen.

669
00:55:40.681 --> 00:55:42.850
Nice of you to come on...

670
00:55:43.017 --> 00:55:44.852
...such short notice.

671
00:55:45.770 --> 00:55:47.271
General Decker...

672
00:55:47.438 --> 00:55:49.857
...it seems I owe you an apology.

673
00:55:50.107 --> 00:55:52.777
We all make mistakes. Mr. President.

674
00:55:52.945 --> 00:55:54.863
Not anymore.

675
00:55:55.197 --> 00:55:58.367
We're going to take charge of this thing!

676
00:55:58.617 --> 00:56:00.994
Excellent. I have prepared the order.

677
00:56:01.703 --> 00:56:02.871
What's this?

678
00:56:02.955 --> 00:56:06.291
Your executive order for full use
of our nuclear deterrent.

679
00:56:09.962 --> 00:56:12.547
Are you crazy? I'm not starting a war!

680
00:56:12.714 --> 00:56:16.802
We're already at war. sir! We have
to nuke them! We must nuke them now!

681
00:56:18.053 --> 00:56:21.473
General Decker. if you do not shut up...

682
00:56:21.890 --> 00:56:24.142
...I'll relieve you of your command.

683
00:56:24.309 --> 00:56:26.144
We must strike now. sir!

684
00:56:26.311 --> 00:56:28.313
Annihilate! Kill! Kill!

685
00:56:28.814 --> 00:56:29.815
Shut up!

686
00:56:29.982 --> 00:56:32.234
Shut up! Shut up!

687
00:56:57.927 --> 00:56:59.095
Now...

688
00:57:00.930 --> 00:57:03.433
...I want the people to know...

689
00:57:03.600 --> 00:57:06.853
...that they still have two out of three
branches of government...

690
00:57:06.936 --> 00:57:09.606
...working for them. and that ain't bad.

691
00:57:09.772 --> 00:57:14.694
I want the people to know
that the schools will still be open. okay?

692
00:57:15.278 --> 00:57:17.614
And I want the people to know...

693
00:57:17.780 --> 00:57:20.867
...that the garbage will still be carried out.

694
00:57:21.034 --> 00:57:22.702
And I want a cop...

695
00:57:22.869 --> 00:57:24.287
...on every corner.

696
00:57:24.370 --> 00:57:26.205
Which. incidentally...

697
00:57:26.372 --> 00:57:28.708
...we would already have...

698
00:57:28.875 --> 00:57:31.878
...if they had listened to me
in the last election.

699
00:57:35.048 --> 00:57:36.382
Jerry...

700
00:57:36.549 --> 00:57:38.718
...how soon can we go on the air?

701
00:57:44.223 --> 00:57:46.726
My fellow Americans.

702
00:57:47.226 --> 00:57:49.395
It is with a heavy heart...

703
00:57:49.562 --> 00:57:51.981
...that I speak to you this afternoon.

704
00:57:52.149 --> 00:57:53.400
As you know...

705
00:57:53.484 --> 00:57:58.405
...earlier today the Martian ambassador
and his confederates...

706
00:57:58.656 --> 00:58:00.407
...attacked and killed...

707
00:58:00.574 --> 00:58:04.745
...many of your representatives
on Capitol Hill.

708
00:58:05.329 --> 00:58:10.000
I will be conferring
with other world leaders as time goes on.

709
00:58:10.751 --> 00:58:14.672
And rest assured that. working together...

710
00:58:15.089 --> 00:58:17.758
...we will soon come out...

711
00:58:18.676 --> 00:58:21.595
...at a very real outcome.

712
00:58:23.847 --> 00:58:25.266
Thank you.

713
00:58:54.296 --> 00:58:56.047
Nathalie. is that you?

714
00:58:56.798 --> 00:58:58.049
Yes.

715
00:58:58.216 --> 00:58:59.384
How're you?

716
00:59:01.428 --> 00:59:03.513
Not terribly good. I'm afraid.

717
00:59:05.390 --> 00:59:07.142
May I ask you a question?

718
00:59:09.978 --> 00:59:11.563
Of course you can.

719
00:59:12.731 --> 00:59:15.150
Were you flirting with me on the show?

720
00:59:15.400 --> 00:59:16.568
Because...

721
00:59:16.818 --> 00:59:18.236
...if you were...

722
00:59:18.320 --> 00:59:20.155
...I just want you to know...

723
00:59:20.238 --> 00:59:22.073
...that I liked it.

724
00:59:23.575 --> 00:59:24.826
You did?

725
00:59:24.993 --> 00:59:25.994
Really?

726
00:59:26.077 --> 00:59:29.497
Because. you know.
I've watched you on TV quite a bit and...

727
00:59:29.581 --> 00:59:30.957
...well. I've...

728
00:59:31.416 --> 00:59:34.419
...had something of
a schoolboycrush on you for...

729
00:59:34.586 --> 00:59:35.837
...oh. gosh...

730
00:59:36.004 --> 00:59:37.255
...ages.

731
01:00:18.381 --> 01:00:19.507
Hi. there.

732
01:00:19.715 --> 01:00:22.134
Are you interested in the White House?

733
01:00:27.306 --> 01:00:29.809
I work there. I'm the press secretary.

734
01:00:29.976 --> 01:00:31.143
Jerry Ross.

735
01:00:31.894 --> 01:00:33.688
Have you ever heard of me?

736
01:00:35.314 --> 01:00:37.942
You wouldn't believe
the pressure of my job.

737
01:00:39.652 --> 01:00:41.821
It's nice to see a new face.

738
01:00:49.579 --> 01:00:50.997
Are you doing anything?

739
01:00:51.081 --> 01:00:53.166
'Cause if you want. I...

740
01:00:53.333 --> 01:00:55.377
...could give you a personalized tour.

741
01:00:55.460 --> 01:00:57.004
Would you like that?

742
01:00:59.381 --> 01:01:02.467
Hey. Mitch. it's me. Can you let me in?

743
01:01:06.305 --> 01:01:08.557
Hello. Mr. Ross. Sure.

744
01:01:08.724 --> 01:01:11.226
We're a little nervous here.
after what happened.

745
01:01:11.310 --> 01:01:12.394
Exactly.

746
01:01:21.737 --> 01:01:24.656
Many great men and women
have passed through here.

747
01:01:25.240 --> 01:01:27.409
Now we're passing through here.

748
01:01:27.910 --> 01:01:29.995
Feels good. don't it?

749
01:01:33.332 --> 01:01:35.167
You're very graceful.

750
01:01:35.918 --> 01:01:37.169
I like that.

751
01:01:44.843 --> 01:01:46.011
Come here.

752
01:02:06.532 --> 01:02:08.618
We call this the Kennedy Room.

753
01:02:12.956 --> 01:02:14.624
Pretty nifty. huh?

754
01:02:47.907 --> 01:02:49.158
So...

755
01:02:49.325 --> 01:02:50.910
...how about a drink?

756
01:03:21.025 --> 01:03:22.943
Getting more comfortable.

757
01:03:25.279 --> 01:03:26.697
Outstanding.

758
01:03:41.211 --> 01:03:42.796
How's my lady doing?

759
01:03:53.141 --> 01:03:55.226
Oh. missy. you're hot.

760
01:03:55.977 --> 01:03:58.396
Could we get that gum out of your mouth?

761
01:04:04.986 --> 01:04:06.321
My finger!

762
01:04:11.493 --> 01:04:14.329
Hello! Hello. operator?
This is an emergency!

763
01:04:14.496 --> 01:04:15.580
Help!

764
01:05:41.417 --> 01:05:42.585
Don't shoot!

765
01:05:47.089 --> 01:05:48.674
Don't worry. darling.

766
01:05:57.517 --> 01:05:58.602
Get down!

767
01:06:08.946 --> 01:06:10.364
Thank you. Mitch.

768
01:06:10.530 --> 01:06:11.740
It's my job.

769
01:07:06.004 --> 01:07:06.921
What's happening?

770
01:07:07.005 --> 01:07:10.425
They appear to be
in a highly agitated state.

771
01:07:10.592 --> 01:07:13.011
And I. I don't know.

772
01:07:13.678 --> 01:07:15.263
I honestly don't know.

773
01:07:15.430 --> 01:07:18.433
I don't know what's going on anymore.
This is frustrating.

774
01:07:18.516 --> 01:07:20.226
I'm not feeling myself.

775
01:07:20.602 --> 01:07:22.687
lf only I could hold you in my arms!

776
01:07:22.770 --> 01:07:24.355
Oh. Donald!

777
01:07:24.522 --> 01:07:26.149
I'm scared!

778
01:08:00.309 --> 01:08:01.393
Excuse me.

779
01:08:01.560 --> 01:08:04.396
You said you wanted to know
as soon as possible.

780
01:08:04.563 --> 01:08:05.648
What is it?

781
01:08:05.731 --> 01:08:06.982
It's NO2.

782
01:08:07.149 --> 01:08:08.901
Highly concentrated.

783
01:08:09.068 --> 01:08:10.402
Nitrogen.

784
01:08:10.903 --> 01:08:12.237
So...

785
01:08:12.488 --> 01:08:15.491
...that's how it could breathe
in our atmosphere.

786
01:08:16.325 --> 01:08:18.160
What's that noise?

787
01:08:50.151 --> 01:08:53.321
But. Theodore.
I simply do not feel that Lincoln....

788
01:08:53.738 --> 01:08:55.407
It's a full-scale invasion.

789
01:08:55.490 --> 01:08:57.242
We must get you to safety.

790
01:09:03.164 --> 01:09:04.416
Not this way?

791
01:09:04.499 --> 01:09:07.002
I'm sorry. there's a tour going through.

792
01:09:07.586 --> 01:09:11.590
The Blue Room is often considered
the most beautiful in the White House.

793
01:09:11.756 --> 01:09:14.926
It is often used by the president
to receive guests.

794
01:09:15.760 --> 01:09:18.763
It is furnished to represent
the period of James Monroe.

795
01:09:18.847 --> 01:09:20.056
What's that?

796
01:09:20.473 --> 01:09:21.808
That...

797
01:09:21.975 --> 01:09:24.561
...is a portrait of James Monroe.

798
01:10:16.447 --> 01:10:17.949
We lost Taffy!

799
01:10:22.536 --> 01:10:26.123
Keep moving.
we must get you to the back stairs!

800
01:10:32.630 --> 01:10:34.548
The Nancy Reagan chandelier!

801
01:10:53.527 --> 01:10:56.530
What are you gawking at?
Get that president out of here!

802
01:11:02.911 --> 01:11:04.913
I personally guarantee...

803
01:11:05.330 --> 01:11:08.792
...that you will get a complete return
on your investment...

804
01:11:08.917 --> 01:11:10.919
...within five months.

805
01:11:11.086 --> 01:11:13.005
Mr. Land. excuse me.

806
01:11:13.171 --> 01:11:16.425
Just a second. Sheik Rakula.

807
01:11:18.427 --> 01:11:19.177
Now...

808
01:11:19.261 --> 01:11:23.432
...even in a time of so-called
intergalactic emergency...

809
01:11:24.600 --> 01:11:25.934
...the people...

810
01:11:26.101 --> 01:11:28.770
...still want to roll them bones!

811
01:11:30.272 --> 01:11:31.773
I believe--

812
01:11:32.274 --> 01:11:34.109
Just five more minutes.

813
01:11:35.027 --> 01:11:38.030
What I'd like for you to do is to...

814
01:11:38.196 --> 01:11:41.533
...view our new.
state-of-the-art show room.

815
01:11:42.868 --> 01:11:45.203
It is out-of-sight!

816
01:11:46.788 --> 01:11:47.915
Gentlemen.

817
01:11:51.961 --> 01:11:53.963
There is no way...

818
01:11:54.130 --> 01:11:55.965
...that we can lose.

819
01:12:41.177 --> 01:12:44.514
''It's not unusual to be loved by anyone

820
01:12:46.349 --> 01:12:49.936
''It's not unusual to have fun with anyone

821
01:12:51.438 --> 01:12:55.025
''But when I see you hanging
about with anyone

822
01:12:56.902 --> 01:12:59.571
''It's not unusual to see me cry

823
01:13:01.490 --> 01:13:03.492
''I want to die''

824
01:13:04.326 --> 01:13:06.161
I've called you all day.

825
01:13:06.328 --> 01:13:07.746
The flight's been canceled.

826
01:13:07.830 --> 01:13:10.332
Byron. there's Martians everywhere!

827
01:13:11.250 --> 01:13:12.209
Hello?

828
01:13:13.836 --> 01:13:15.254
I can't hear you!

829
01:13:20.884 --> 01:13:22.636
I must get to Washington.

830
01:13:27.725 --> 01:13:29.518
Do you know anyone who can fly a plane?

831
01:13:29.602 --> 01:13:30.769
Your husband. Art.

832
01:13:30.853 --> 01:13:31.937
He's dead.

833
01:13:32.104 --> 01:13:33.647
I told him this would happen.

834
01:13:33.731 --> 01:13:35.899
I loaded the plane with supplies.

835
01:13:36.191 --> 01:13:40.529
I want to go to the Tahoe caves.
It's remote. the Martians won't find it.

836
01:13:40.946 --> 01:13:41.947
Where's the plane?

837
01:13:42.031 --> 01:13:44.783
Private airfield. Other side of the freeway.

838
01:13:44.950 --> 01:13:46.702
Will it fly to Washington?

839
01:13:46.869 --> 01:13:48.704
I want to go to Tahoe.

840
01:13:48.871 --> 01:13:50.706
''You find it happens

841
01:13:50.874 --> 01:13:53.043
''All the time

842
01:13:53.627 --> 01:13:56.046
''Love will never do

843
01:13:56.713 --> 01:13:58.715
''What you want it to

844
01:13:59.633 --> 01:14:01.635
''Why can't this crazy love

845
01:14:02.052 --> 01:14:04.054
''Be mine''

846
01:14:12.979 --> 01:14:14.314
Jesus Christ!

847
01:14:23.365 --> 01:14:24.866
Girls. get out!

848
01:14:34.125 --> 01:14:36.544
There's a Martian right behind me!

849
01:14:36.711 --> 01:14:39.381
You're Tom Jones! ''It Ain't Unusual.''

850
01:14:40.548 --> 01:14:41.633
Autograph?

851
01:14:41.716 --> 01:14:43.843
Anybody got a pen?

852
01:15:01.988 --> 01:15:03.322
Great punch.

853
01:15:03.489 --> 01:15:04.907
You'll need that gun.

854
01:15:04.991 --> 01:15:06.742
-I'm Tom Jones.
-Byron Williams.

855
01:15:06.826 --> 01:15:09.078
I saw you fight in Cardiff. Wales.

856
01:15:10.413 --> 01:15:11.581
You okay?

857
01:15:11.998 --> 01:15:14.250
-I need a drink.
-You and me both.

858
01:15:14.417 --> 01:15:16.419
-We better go.
-Can you fly a plane?

859
01:15:16.502 --> 01:15:17.420
Sure. Got one?

860
01:15:17.503 --> 01:15:18.588
She has.

861
01:15:38.107 --> 01:15:40.860
Don't run. we are your friends.

862
01:16:11.892 --> 01:16:13.477
Martians blew up the shop!

863
01:16:13.560 --> 01:16:14.478
You're kidding.

864
01:16:14.561 --> 01:16:15.646
Should I get Grandma?

865
01:16:15.729 --> 01:16:19.232
Forget her! She's halfway
to outer space already! Here!

866
01:16:19.399 --> 01:16:22.569
I'll tell you one thing.
They ain't getting the TV!

867
01:16:26.239 --> 01:16:29.076
The president of France is on line two.

868
01:16:32.913 --> 01:16:36.166
Mr. President. the president of France
is on line two.

869
01:16:36.333 --> 01:16:38.168
He says it's important.

870
01:16:43.757 --> 01:16:45.926
Hello. Maurice.

871
01:16:48.595 --> 01:16:50.264
I have good news.

872
01:16:50.431 --> 01:16:51.933
The Martian ambassador is here.

873
01:16:52.016 --> 01:16:54.269
We've negotiated a settlement.

874
01:16:56.271 --> 01:16:58.606
Maurice get out of the room.

875
01:16:58.773 --> 01:17:00.275
Get out. now!

876
01:17:45.903 --> 01:17:47.155
Mr. President.

877
01:17:49.575 --> 01:17:51.327
Mr. President.

878
01:17:51.493 --> 01:17:54.079
I need you to sign this!

879
01:17:58.834 --> 01:18:00.336
What is it?

880
01:18:00.502 --> 01:18:02.922
My last will and testament?

881
01:18:03.088 --> 01:18:07.092
It is an order to deploy
our nuclear capability. sir.

882
01:19:18.915 --> 01:19:20.834
What the hell was that?

883
01:21:03.146 --> 01:21:04.064
Look!

884
01:21:11.488 --> 01:21:12.739
What was that?

885
01:21:14.783 --> 01:21:15.867
Where you going?

886
01:21:15.951 --> 01:21:17.035
To get Grandma.

887
01:21:17.119 --> 01:21:19.079
Stay and defend this trailer!

888
01:21:19.162 --> 01:21:21.290
That's what Billy-Glenn would do.

889
01:21:21.456 --> 01:21:23.041
You're disgracing a hero!

890
01:21:23.125 --> 01:21:25.627
I don't care. I'm gonna go get grandma.

891
01:21:26.295 --> 01:21:27.671
Come back here!

892
01:21:40.976 --> 01:21:42.728
What in the hell is that?

893
01:21:50.194 --> 01:21:51.529
Cut it out!

894
01:21:57.035 --> 01:21:58.411
Stop it!

895
01:22:07.337 --> 01:22:08.463
-This way!
-No. this way!

896
01:22:08.546 --> 01:22:11.007
It's a short cut! The airfield's--

897
01:22:11.174 --> 01:22:13.676
Bullshit! The airfield's over there!

898
01:22:19.515 --> 01:22:23.436
Being dressed like King Tut
doesn't make you our leader!

899
01:22:23.561 --> 01:22:25.063
Look. this is wrong!

900
01:22:25.229 --> 01:22:29.067
We're lost! He led us down a maze!
I'm going back to the hotel.

901
01:22:29.233 --> 01:22:30.568
-This way!
-Wait!

902
01:22:30.735 --> 01:22:32.570
Where are you going?

903
01:22:32.737 --> 01:22:33.488
Come on.

904
01:22:33.571 --> 01:22:35.073
But. I like him.

905
01:22:41.537 --> 01:22:45.875
Assholes! Why'd I listen to them?
I should have stayed in the hotel.

906
01:22:46.459 --> 01:22:47.877
Shit!

907
01:22:50.589 --> 01:22:52.091
I surrender. okay?

908
01:22:52.591 --> 01:22:54.885
You understand what that means?

909
01:22:56.095 --> 01:22:58.764
Look! You're intelligent beings.

910
01:22:59.390 --> 01:23:01.600
Let's cut a deal. I can help.

911
01:23:01.767 --> 01:23:03.227
I'm a lawyer!

912
01:23:03.560 --> 01:23:06.981
You want to conquer the world.
you'll need lawyers. right?

913
01:23:08.607 --> 01:23:09.608
Here.

914
01:23:10.484 --> 01:23:12.111
You want my watch?

915
01:23:12.611 --> 01:23:15.281
Take it. Take it. It's a Rolex!

916
01:23:25.791 --> 01:23:27.251
Nice shot!

917
01:23:27.418 --> 01:23:28.836
Pity I was too late.

918
01:23:28.919 --> 01:23:30.796
Can I have the gun back?

919
01:23:31.005 --> 01:23:32.923
Give me the gun and come on!

920
01:24:47.707 --> 01:24:48.708
Grandma!

921
01:24:57.093 --> 01:24:58.386
Oh. my God!

922
01:25:12.525 --> 01:25:14.902
I think these guys are very sick.

923
01:25:15.736 --> 01:25:18.447
What's happening to them?
What's killing them?

924
01:25:19.907 --> 01:25:22.285
I think it must be my music.

925
01:25:30.084 --> 01:25:31.502
Quiet!

926
01:26:23.138 --> 01:26:25.724
You think you can do anything you want.

927
01:26:25.891 --> 01:26:27.309
You can't.

928
01:26:27.476 --> 01:26:28.310
Because...

929
01:26:28.393 --> 01:26:30.646
...we are human...

930
01:26:30.979 --> 01:26:31.980
...beings.

931
01:26:32.064 --> 01:26:35.651
And we have the United States Army...

932
01:26:36.652 --> 01:26:38.236
...that'll fight you...

933
01:26:38.320 --> 01:26:42.407
...to the last man!
And we'll never surrender!

934
01:26:46.244 --> 01:26:47.829
Do you hear me?

935
01:26:47.997 --> 01:26:50.917
We'll fight you on the beaches.
We'll fight you in the streets.

936
01:26:51.000 --> 01:26:53.503
We will never. never surrender!

937
01:26:53.670 --> 01:26:56.005
We will win!

938
01:26:56.172 --> 01:26:58.007
Democracy will survive!

939
01:26:58.258 --> 01:27:00.093
We will never. ever...

940
01:27:00.260 --> 01:27:01.844
...surrender!

941
01:27:02.011 --> 01:27:03.346
We will win!

942
01:27:03.513 --> 01:27:05.515
The eagle will be triumphant!

943
01:27:35.545 --> 01:27:37.046
Why...

944
01:27:37.297 --> 01:27:39.048
...are you doing this?

945
01:27:41.134 --> 01:27:42.302
Why?

946
01:27:43.469 --> 01:27:46.222
lsn't the universe big enough...

947
01:27:46.806 --> 01:27:48.474
...for both of us?

948
01:27:52.396 --> 01:27:54.481
What is wrong with you people?

949
01:27:57.401 --> 01:27:59.069
We could work together.

950
01:28:00.237 --> 01:28:02.323
Why be enemies?

951
01:28:03.324 --> 01:28:05.075
Because we're different?

952
01:28:06.160 --> 01:28:07.828
Is that why?

953
01:28:11.999 --> 01:28:14.668
Think of the things that we could do.

954
01:28:16.086 --> 01:28:19.006
Think how strong we would be!

955
01:28:20.841 --> 01:28:22.343
Earth...

956
01:28:23.177 --> 01:28:25.095
...and Mars...

957
01:28:26.180 --> 01:28:27.431
...together.

958
01:28:30.059 --> 01:28:32.895
There is nothing
that we could not accomplish.

959
01:28:33.938 --> 01:28:35.689
Think about it!

960
01:28:37.942 --> 01:28:39.860
Think about it!

961
01:28:41.362 --> 01:28:43.030
Why destroy...

962
01:28:43.864 --> 01:28:46.033
...when you can create?

963
01:28:47.368 --> 01:28:49.370
We can have it all...

964
01:28:50.205 --> 01:28:52.624
...or we can smash it all!

965
01:28:56.127 --> 01:28:57.629
Why can't we...

966
01:28:57.879 --> 01:29:00.131
...work out our differences?

967
01:29:01.383 --> 01:29:03.301
Why can't we...

968
01:29:03.635 --> 01:29:05.804
...work things out?

969
01:29:08.306 --> 01:29:10.475
Little people...

970
01:29:12.811 --> 01:29:14.896
...why can't we all just...

971
01:29:16.147 --> 01:29:17.899
...get along?

972
01:29:44.759 --> 01:29:45.969
What's this?

973
01:30:24.216 --> 01:30:26.802
Don't run. We are your friends.

974
01:30:28.387 --> 01:30:30.973
Don't run. We are your friends.

975
01:30:44.445 --> 01:30:46.280
Next stop. radio station.

976
01:30:49.201 --> 01:30:50.702
There it is!

977
01:30:51.370 --> 01:30:52.955
Let's move it!

978
01:31:10.889 --> 01:31:12.224
There it is.

979
01:31:13.558 --> 01:31:15.644
Go start it. Go with him.

980
01:31:15.811 --> 01:31:17.396
Cindy. come with me.

981
01:31:34.663 --> 01:31:36.248
Are you sure you can fly this?

982
01:31:36.331 --> 01:31:38.000
I think so. yeah.

983
01:31:40.419 --> 01:31:41.837
Who put that on?

984
01:31:43.171 --> 01:31:45.924
-It's stuck!
-Cindy. over here.

985
01:31:52.432 --> 01:31:53.600
Shit!

986
01:31:54.517 --> 01:31:56.853
They haven't seen us yet. Come here.

987
01:31:58.938 --> 01:32:00.356
Get in the plane.

988
01:32:00.773 --> 01:32:02.609
I'll distract them.

989
01:32:02.775 --> 01:32:05.028
The first chance you get. go.

990
01:32:05.194 --> 01:32:07.363
-I'm not leaving you!
-Just do it!

991
01:32:07.447 --> 01:32:09.449
I'll draw them away! Go!

992
01:32:09.616 --> 01:32:10.700
No!

993
01:32:10.867 --> 01:32:12.285
I said go!

994
01:32:17.040 --> 01:32:18.625
Oh. my God!

995
01:32:19.459 --> 01:32:20.793
What's he doing?

996
01:32:20.877 --> 01:32:21.794
He's flipped!

997
01:32:21.878 --> 01:32:23.796
He's going to throw them off
so we can escape.

998
01:32:23.880 --> 01:32:25.381
We can't leave him!

999
01:32:28.551 --> 01:32:29.636
No weapon!

1000
01:32:29.969 --> 01:32:32.138
No clown outfit!

1001
01:32:32.305 --> 01:32:33.556
Just me!

1002
01:32:34.140 --> 01:32:35.558
Byron Williams...

1003
01:32:36.225 --> 01:32:38.478
...heavyweight champion...

1004
01:32:39.062 --> 01:32:40.730
...of the world!

1005
01:33:51.428 --> 01:33:53.513
Something's happened.

1006
01:33:53.805 --> 01:33:55.890
Something's happened to Byron.

1007
01:34:12.282 --> 01:34:14.868
''When I'm calling you

1008
01:34:36.473 --> 01:34:40.018
''That means I offer my love to you''

1009
01:35:17.431 --> 01:35:18.849
Good-bye. my darling.

1010
01:35:18.933 --> 01:35:20.893
I wish things were different.

1011
01:35:21.686 --> 01:35:23.354
So do I.

1012
01:35:28.943 --> 01:35:30.278
Good-bye.

1013
01:35:30.695 --> 01:35:31.779
I love you.

1014
01:35:31.862 --> 01:35:33.781
I love you too. Nathalie.

1015
01:37:09.545 --> 01:37:11.130
Florence Norris...

1016
01:37:11.297 --> 01:37:14.467
...I present to you
the Congressional Medal of Honor...

1017
01:37:14.634 --> 01:37:16.886
...the nation's highest decoration.

1018
01:37:18.805 --> 01:37:22.392
Thank you.
but don't you dare let this happen again!

1019
01:37:23.893 --> 01:37:25.645
Richard Norris...

1020
01:37:25.812 --> 01:37:28.815
...on behalf of my parents.
who couldn't be here today...

1021
01:37:28.898 --> 01:37:31.401
...for saving the world from the Martians...

1022
01:37:31.484 --> 01:37:33.987
...I present to you the Medal of Honor.

1023
01:37:34.821 --> 01:37:36.906
Don't kiss me if you don't want.

1024
01:37:37.323 --> 01:37:38.825
I have to.

1025
01:37:41.995 --> 01:37:44.330
I prepared a speech. Is that okay?

1026
01:37:45.081 --> 01:37:47.166
Sure. that's very appropriate.

1027
01:37:52.006 --> 01:37:53.257
Hi. everybody.

1028
01:37:54.675 --> 01:37:55.926
I want to say--

1029
01:37:56.010 --> 01:37:58.596
Can you speak up? We can't hear you.

1030
01:37:59.096 --> 01:38:02.433
I want to say that there's
a lot of people in the world...

1031
01:38:02.516 --> 01:38:05.436
...that have done a lot more
than I have. and...

1032
01:38:05.603 --> 01:38:07.771
...they should be here now...

1033
01:38:08.022 --> 01:38:09.523
...getting a medal.

1034
01:38:11.525 --> 01:38:13.694
And I want to thank my grandma...

1035
01:38:13.861 --> 01:38:16.030
...for always being good to me...

1036
01:38:16.196 --> 01:38:19.116
...and for helping save the world
and everything.

1037
01:38:20.284 --> 01:38:23.537
So. I guess. like. now we just have to...

1038
01:38:23.704 --> 01:38:27.708
...start over and start rebuilding
everything. like our houses.

1039
01:38:27.875 --> 01:38:32.796
But I was thinking. maybe instead
of houses we could live in tepees.

1040
01:38:33.130 --> 01:38:35.299
Because it's better in many ways.

1041
01:38:38.886 --> 01:38:41.555
That's all I have to say. Thanks.

1042
01:38:43.474 --> 01:38:44.725
Was that okay?

1043
01:38:44.808 --> 01:38:45.893
Yeah.

1044
01:38:46.728 --> 01:38:48.438
Do you got a girlfriend?

1045
01:38:48.647 --> 01:38:49.648
No.

1046
01:38:51.066 --> 01:38:54.152
Give me a break.
Go on in there and clean your room.

1047
01:38:54.319 --> 01:38:56.988
I can't do this all by myself. Look at you.

1048
